The paper discusses the analysis of a repeated game with random state information, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of communication and encoding techniques in the game suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the role of randomization and the importance of higher rates of communication, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper considers the optimal performance of a game with a helper transmitting state information, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
